proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.writing

Class WriterFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.writing.WriterFactory

  • public class WriterFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used for writing the data. It has a List of all possible Writers, and generates a new Writer for each task it is given.

      • write

        public static void write(OutputConfiguration outputConf,
         Intern data)
                  throws InvalidInputException
        This is the method that initiates the writing. It generates a new Writer, and calls its write method.
        Parameters:
        outputConf - The OutputConfiguration that describes how the data shall be written.
        data - The data to write
        Throws:
        InvalidInputException - Throws the exception that Writer.write(proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.description.OutputConfiguration, proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.description.Intern) has thrown to it.

      • getWriterFromType

        public static Writer getWriterFromType(java.lang.String type)
                                throws InvalidInputException
        Returns the Writer out of the List of all possible Writers, that has the specified type. Does NOT generate a new Writer, so the Writer returned by this should not be modified.
        Parameters:
        type - The type of the Writer that shall be returned
        Returns:
        The Writer with the specified type
        Throws:
        InvalidInputException - If no Writer of the given type exists
